    "narrative": "Today\u2019s lineup for **Ghost Ride the WHIP** is anchored by a high-upside outfield stack, led by **Mickey Moniak** (75.98) and **Corbin Carroll** (71.33). **Mickey Moniak** is the clear standout play; the combination of a massive 14% park factor boost and the platoon advantage against Sasaki creates an elite environment for production. **Corbin Carroll** remains a core tactical piece, as his efficiency holds strong even against a high-caliber arm like Gausman. In the middle infield, **Max Muncy** (61.16) and **Brice Turang** (59.72) provide essential stability. **Brice Turang** is particularly intriguing today; his 100% stolen base efficiency against a slower pitcher\u2019s delivery adds critical value in our hunt for the scarcest category in this 5x5 format.\n\nWe are navigating a few tactical risks, most notably the matchup for **Jose Caballero** (52.65). While his dynamic platoon edge against the lefty keeps him rostered, his efficiency is suppressed by facing Ragans\u2014a top-tier arm with a 2.52 xERA. On the bench, **Alex Freeland** (52.07) was the most difficult exclusion. He nearly cracked the starting nine thanks to a +14% park adjustment, but his position in the bottom of the order and lower base projection relegated him to the bench in favor of the higher-scoring profiles of **Tyler Soderstrom** and **Austin Riley**. Meanwhile, **Vinnie Pasquantino** (51.32) was penalized by a stiff 15% drop due to his matchup against the southpaw Weathers, reinforcing our disciplined approach to platoon splits.\n\nAs the day progresses, keep an eye on the battery dynamics for **James Wood** (66.69) and **Austin Riley** (65.87). Both face elite catchers with quick pop times, which has marginally dampened their ceiling in our model. **Tyler Soderstrom** (53.24) remains a marginal play; despite the favorable park, the platoon disadvantage against Schultz limits his output potential. We are holding **Luis Campusano** (34.25) below the floor today, as his matchup against Urena doesn't offer enough volume or efficiency to justify a start. With **Giancarlo Stanton** currently out of the lineup, our bench depth will be tested, but the projected performance of the starters should keep us competitive across all five categories.",
